{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/background-information/causes/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"955fe314-c2f6-59b3-b2db-3e1696f263db","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field c17bc56f-368b-4f2a-971b-4a11b2ecf2f8 --><h2>What causes it?</h2><!-- end field c17bc56f-368b-4f2a-971b-4a11b2ecf2f8 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 560f6c9c-538d-43c4-9d32-5021e5daa707 --><!-- begin field f3a496e4-646e-40bd-93bc-800fd1fe50d3 --><ul><li><strong>Non-septic bursitis</strong><ul><li>Non-infectious causes of bursitis include trauma, overuse, gout, and systemic disease such as rheumatoid arthritis, systemic lupus erythematosus, and sarcoidosis.</li><li>Factors associated with the development of non-septic bursitis include:<ul><li>Acute trauma such as a fall directly onto the patella.</li><li>Repetitive microtrauma from overuse with any activity involving prolonged kneeling or leaning against the knee, for example coal mining, carpet laying, gardening, roofing, cleaning or wrestling.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><strong>Septic bursitis</strong><ul><li>The pre-patellar bursa can become infected by direct inoculation of micro-organisms from overlying skin lesions, local trauma, and cellulitis or rarely by haematogenous seeding.<ul><li>Approximately 80% of cases of septic bursitis are due to infection with <em>Staphylococcus aureus</em> (in some cases community acquired methicillin-resistant <em>Staphylococcus aureus</em> [MRSA]).</li><li>Many other organisms including other Staphylococcal, Streptococcal, Mycobacterial, and fungal species can also cause septic bursitis.</li></ul></li><li>Predisposing factors for septic bursitis include a history of trauma to the bursa or surrounding area, diabetes, alcohol excess, immunocompromise (for example hypogammaglobinaemia or HIV/AIDS), and chronic kidney disease.<ul><li>Up to half of all cases of septic bursitis occur in immunocompromised people.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">Reid, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">Aaron et al, 2011</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">Huang, 2011</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">Chalmers, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">Le Manac&#39;h, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">Hanrahan, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">Baumbach et al, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">Hong, 2014</a>]</p><!-- end field f3a496e4-646e-40bd-93bc-800fd1fe50d3 --><!-- end item 560f6c9c-538d-43c4-9d32-5021e5daa707 -->","topic":{"id":"7c029d3e-557f-550b-885f-a4fbb6ea8b1a","topicId":"54c9032c-42d1-4a7e-aa9b-60cc7c1f66b7","topicName":"Pre-patellar bursitis","slug":"pre-patellar-bursitis","lastRevised":"Last revised in December 2016","chapters":[{"id":"a3d36f54-4e47-50ed-adae-8c2966e52581","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"bace3ffb-9b9e-509e-8531-d66d3c3c62b8","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"f4c8ac50-2d63-5270-a56e-0a3146cc2f4b","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"b2ab9579-f5ec-589c-81d9-3041f5c94af1","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"98917828-0ada-5354-9717-48e2b11fef87","slug":"update","fullIt